title: Print, "The Dinner Horn", June 11, 1870
medium: Wood engraving printed in black ink on paper
provenance: Gift of Mrs. Cora E. Wilson
description: Vertical view at left of the corner of a house with an open door showing portion of interior where a table is laid for a meal, at center of a woman with her back turned blowing trumpet, and in the distance beyond a well with sweep and a field with workers.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "The Dinner Horn", June 11, 1870.
June 11, 1870. Wood engraving printed in black ink on paper. Gift of Cora Wilson. 1939-70-5.
